At Above Average Joe, we believe in quality control.  Quality Control, for us, begins with solid requirement engineering.  We plan to work with the RE engineers and developers to get the RE as close to perfect as RE goes.  We believe that if we can get a quality RE process, that quality effect will trickle down to the development cycle.  

Another way we planned for quality control is through testing. Testing will be integrated throughout the development process.  We will also explore user acceptance testing via beta releases to see if there are errors and bugs that we missed during development.  Our philosophy is that testing is constant: that is we will have a channel of communication open to our users so they can give us real time feedbacks.

One way of measurement is to have criteria set forth to define what is meant by high quality.  In this our case, we are developing an app with certain expectations.  If the app met all expectations without any errors or bugs, it is suffice to say that the app is of high quality from the developers point of view.  

However, as we are in the business to make money, the ultimate measurement of high quality will be from user acceptance and monetary success.
